usage: word_count.py [-h] [--json] [-n CUTOFF] textfile

positional arguments:
  textfile       text file to analyze

optional arguments:
  --json         display results in JSON format
  -n CUTOFF      number of "most common" words to show (defaults to 10)
 

Notes:

Python version: 2.7.15

I've included one file, 57110-0.txt, to run the script against.

Tests are in tests.py, and can be run with the command `python -m unittest tests`
tests.py utilizes the file aesop.txt

Other notes are expressed as comments in word_count.py

